SUMMARY:Suicide Prevention Training for Pediatric Health Clinicians: SAFETY
 -A Level 2
LOCATION:Virtual
DESCRIPTION:Offered by the Texas Child Mental Health Care Consortium \, the
  SAFETY-A Suicide Risk Assessment Training is designed to equip primary ca
 re providers with the critical skills needed to recognize when it’s time t
 o implement SAFETY-A — a family-centered intervention developed by researc
 hers at the UCLA ASAP Center for youth who have attempted suicide\, engage
 d in self-harm behaviors or expressed strong suicidal urges. This comprehe
 nsive program demonstrates how to identify and address suicide risk effect
 ively\, ensuring timely and appropriate interventions for those in need. S
 AFETY-A Level 2 training involves attending one three-hour master training
  to learn about how to use the SAFETY-A intervention in a primary care set
 ting. The master training includes a didactic portion as well as videos an
 d opportunities to role play using SAFETY-A with patients. This option is 
 for PCPs who want to develop a foundational-level knowledge of SAFETY-A. L
 earn more and register . For questions\, email Kate Foshee .\\n\\nRegister
  »: https://bcmpsych.sjc1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_56odypzTpdbdTlc\\nregi
 ster: http://bcmpsych.sjc1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_56odypzTpdbdTlc\\n\\n
 Event page: https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/suicide-prevention-training-
 for-pediatric-health-clinicians-safety-a-level-2-041026
URL:https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/suicide-prevention-training-for-pedia
 tric-health-clinicians-safety-a-level-2-041026
END:VEVENT
