BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1e1d5da2-127f-5b66-9462-492b306cdcf6
DTSTAMP:20260326T210201Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260410T083000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260410T093000
SUMMARY:Pediatric Grand Rounds: Reflections on Parenting
LOCATION:Hybrid: Dell Children’s Medical Center Signe Auditorium & Zoom
DESCRIPTION:In this installment of Pediatric Grand Rounds and the fifth ann
 ual George Edwards Lectureship\, Andrea G. Asnes \, M.D.\, MSW\, presents 
 “Reflections on Parenting: Adequacy\, Threats to Adequacy\, and the Impact
  of Practice\, Programs and Policies.” Asnes is a professor in the Departm
 ent of Pediatrics at Yale School of Medicine. She was also the chief in th
 e section of Child Safety\, Advocacy and Healing in the Department of Pedi
 atrics at the Yale New-Haven Hospital. Email Pam Knight for the Zoom link.
 \\n\\nEvent page: https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/pediatric-grand-rounds
 -reflections-on-parenting
URL:https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/pediatric-grand-rounds-reflections-on
 -parenting
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
