DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260428T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260428T180000
SUMMARY:Neurosurgery Grand Rounds: Neurostimulation as Network Physiology
LOCATION:Hybrid: Health Discovery Building Auditorium (HDB 1.208) & Zoom
DESCRIPTION:In this installment of Neurosurgery Grand Rounds\, Oren Sagher 
 \, M.D.\, presents “Neurostimulation as Network Physiology: Reframing Modu
 lation of Cerebral Blood Flow.” Sagher serves as a professor in the Depart
 ment of Neurosurgery and the director of the Neuromodulation Program at th
 e University of Michigan Medical School. Email Matthew Philbrook for the Z
 oom information.\\n\\nEvent page: https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/neuros
 urgery-grand-rounds-neurostimulation-as-network-physiology
URL:https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/neurosurgery-grand-rounds-neurostimul
 ation-as-network-physiology
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d900f5f8-71f0-5d8d-aad6-21374fb5e304
DTSTAMP:20260326T210201Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260414T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260414T140000
SUMMARY:CPAN Series: What Every PCP Should Know About Autism Spectrum Disor
 ders
LOCATION:Virtual
DESCRIPTION:In this installment of the CPAN Webinar Series\, Jane Ripperger
 -Suhler \, M.D.\, presents “Autism Spectrum Disorders: What Every PCP Shou
 ld Know.” Suhler is an associate professor in the Department of Psychiatry
  and Behavioral Sciences at Dell Medical School. Register to attend. The s
 eries is a program of the Texas Child Mental Health Care Consortium ’s Chi
 ld Psychiatry Access Network and is designed for primary care providers or
  individuals working in pediatric care environments. This series aims to e
 nhance primary care physicians’ capabilities in recognizing and managing m
 ental health conditions to improve outcomes for youth within their clinica
 l practice. PCPs currently demonstrate a significant gap in knowledge and 
 clinical competence regarding the identification and management of mental 
 health disorders in youth. This professional practice gap is primarily att
 ributed to insufficient training and limited access to mental health resou
 rces. As a result\, PCPs often serve as the first point of contact for fam
 ilies dealing with adolescent mental and behavioral health issues\, yet th
 ey report lacking the necessary skills to effectively screen\, assess and 
 treat conditions such as depression\, anxiety\, suicidal ideation and beha
 vioral disorders. For more information about the event\, email cpd@bcm.edu
  .\\n\\nRegister: https://events.teams.microsoft.com/event/e226cefe-d74b-4
 5ad-b253-659e2e10fde7@a83dba53-124d-4d32-88f0-b72889a9e926\\n\\nEvent page
 : https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/cpan-series-what-every-pcp-should-know
 -about-autism-spectrum-disorders
URL:https://dellmed.utexas.edu/events/cpan-series-what-every-pcp-should-kno
 w-about-autism-spectrum-disorders
END:VEVENT
